  "prompt": "Why does the Samsung Galaxy Note 7 explode?",
  "response": "The Samsung Galaxy Note 7 experienced a widespread issue with battery explosions, which led to a global recall of the device in 2016. The primary reasons for the explosions were related to defects in the batteries and design flaws in the phone itself. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the key factors:\n\n1. **Battery Design and Manufacturing Issues**:\n   - The batteries were a mix of those produced by Samsung's subsidiary, Samsung SDI, and another supplier, Amperex Technology Limited (ATL).\n   - The batteries from Samsung SDI were found to have a critical design flaw: the internal separators (thin insulating layers between the positive and negative electrodes) were too thin, which increased the risk of short-circuiting.\n   - Additionally, some batteries had sharp internal edges or insufficient insulation, which could cause a short circuit.\n\n2. **Compromised Internal Space**:\n   - The Note 7 was designed to be sleek and powerful, which led to tightly packed internal components.\n   - This tight design left little room for the battery to expand, which is a normal occurrence during charging and discharging cycles. The lack of space increased the risk of the battery being punctured or damaged.\n\n3. **External Pressure and Heat**:\n   - The combination of these design flaws made the batteries more susceptible to overheating when exposed to external pressure or heat.\n   - Once a short circuit occurred, it could lead to a rapid increase in temperature, causing the battery to catch fire or explode.\n\n4. **Testing and Quality Control**:\n   - Samsung\u2019s testing and quality control processes failed to identify these issues before the phone\u2019s release. This oversight contributed to the widespread nature of the problem.\n\nIn response to the crisis, Samsung launched an extensive investigation, recalled all Note 7 devices, and implemented stricter quality control measures for future products. The incident also led to the development of an 8-point battery safety check for all Samsung devices.",
